    Log of Means between three samples

    logofMeans.between.ABC.Rd

    Computes the mean of each sample, fold change, and log fold change.

    logofMeans.between.ABC(dat, A.samples, B.samples, C.samples)

    Arguments

    dat

    a dataframe. Differential analysis results from "DESeqCalculation"

    A.samples

    First sample type

    B.samples

    Second sample type

    C.samples

    Third sample type

    Value

    log2 fold change of means between three given samples

    Examples

    dat <- matrix(rnorm(600, sd = 0.3), ncol = 9)
#> Warning: data length [600] is not a sub-multiple or multiple of the number of rows [67]
dat <- as.data.frame(dat)
logofMeans.between.ABC(dat = dat, A.samples = 1:3, B.samples = 4:6, C.samples = 7:9)
